% SECTION 2: SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
% ============================================================
\clearpage
\section{System Architecture Overview}

LifeSphere operates as a single distributed intelligence system across five hardware nodes sharing one unified data backbone. The architecture follows a publish-subscribe model with Firebase Realtime Database as the central biological state synchronization layer. Vital32 continuously writes physiological data to the shared state object. All remaining subsystems subscribe to relevant state fields and execute responses within a target latency of 150 milliseconds.

\subsection{Ecosystems Overview \& Functionality}

\subsubsection*{Vital32: The Sensing Layer}
\textbf{How it Works:} Vital32 continuously monitors the user's physiological state using a 16-sensor array. It processes raw ADC readings, applies signal processing like HRV calculation, and feeds the data into multi-timescale AI models.

\textbf{How it is Used:} Worn by the user, it operates invisibly, requiring no interaction. It acts as the biological heartbeat of the entire ecosystem.

\textbf{Humanity Impact:} By shifting healthcare from reactive to proactive, Vital32 detects anomalies and predicts medical emergencies (like seizures or immune activation) hours or days before they become critical, saving lives through early intervention.

