\section{HollowRover: Complete Build Guide}

HollowRover is the autonomous physical response unit of LifeSphere. It runs ROS2 Humble on a D-Robotics RDK X5 (4GB) and uses a dual-layer navigation architecture combining SLAM and UWB precision localization. The drivetrain employs a four-wheel rocker suspension with spring-loaded pivots and a rear differential bar for maintained ground contact over uneven surfaces. A 6-DOF robotic arm provides caregiving assistance and passive security barrier functionality.

